From 7abb046a22899367e971d27823659a7f7403bf5b Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: scholzri <33288574+scholzri@users.noreply.github.com>
Date: Sun, 1 Mar 2026 15:00:03 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] fix(gpio): fix WRITE_BIT double-BIT in actas_gpio pin
 configure
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

WRITE_BIT(var, bit, set) internally applies BIT(bit), so passing
BIT(pin) as the bit argument results in BIT(BIT(pin)). For pins >= 3
this overflows uint8_t and no bit is set, leaving the pin in its
alternate function mode instead of GPIO mode.

Fix by passing pin directly, matching the OEN and IE calls nearby.

Affected: PE4-PE7 (JTAG), PA3 — all stuck in alternate function.
Symptom: kscan matrix columns 0-3 and 7 never drive, no key events.

Co-Authored-By: Claude Opus 4.6 <noreply@anthropic.com>
---
 drivers/gpio/gpio_b91.c | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/drivers/gpio/gpio_b91.c b/drivers/gpio/gpio_b91.c
index b4d9a16236..a791e0577b 100644
--- a/drivers/gpio/gpio_b91.c
+++ b/drivers/gpio/gpio_b91.c
@@ -334,7 +334,7 @@ static int gpio_b91_pin_configure(const struct device *dev,
 	}
 
 	/* GPIO function enable */
-	WRITE_BIT(gpio->actas_gpio, BIT(pin), 1);
+	WRITE_BIT(gpio->actas_gpio, pin, 1);
 
 	/* Set GPIO pull-up / pull-down resistors */
 	gpio_b91_config_up_down_res(gpio, pin, flags);
-- 
